Summary: the Galois group of the Galois field extension $L/K$.
Processed main note contents: If $L/K$ is a Galois field extension, then its Galois group $\operatorname{Gal}(L/K)$ is the group of automorphisms of $L$ fixing $K$ pointwise.

Summary: the dual of the $R$-module $M$. It is defined as $\operatorname{Hom}_R(R,M)$
Processed main note contents: Let $M$ be an $R$-module. We define the dual module $M^\vee$ as $\operatorname{Hom}_R(M,R)$. In other words, $M^\vee$ is the set of all $R$-module homomorphisms $M \to R$. Note that $M^\vee$ has a natural $R$-module structure given by $$(f+g)(m) = f(m) + g(m), \quad (cf)(m) = c f(m).$$

Summary: the finite field of $q$ elements, where $q$ is a power of a prime.
Processed main note contents: Theorem. Let $q$ be a prime power. There is a unique field, up to isomorphism, with $q$ elements. We denote this field as $\mathbb{F}_q$ and call it the "finite field of $q$ elements".
